{"all_questions_require_answer":true,"name":"WMT LEXINGTON - Walmart Saver QC Shop Project - 4.6.14 Week 10 (Save-A-Lot)","qc_comments":"All four corners of the receipt must be visible, otherwise DENY.","objective":"","id":67684,"instructions":"*IT IS CRITICAL THAT YOU READ AND FOLLOW THESE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY.* 

*You will NOT be paid for this job if you do NOT complete it correctly. *

*This job will require you to purchase at least $40 worth of items. 

If you complete the job as requested, we will pay you $6. In addition, we will reimburse you with $45 to cover the cost of your purchases! Can you say, "Free Shopping Trip to Walmart!"*

*The $45 payment transaction may take a few days to show up in your Field Agent account.*


INSTRUCTIONS:

Before going to the WALMART location listed, please pick up a current Print Ad (circular) from the following retailer (Competitor Store):

   - Save-A-Lot

*You will need a printed copy. A digital version will NOT work.

Please make sure that the Print Ad is from a store that is within 5 miles of the Walmart location you will be shopping. One of the above stores should be nearby.

There are additional instructions in the job that will direct you through this shopping trip. 

In general, you will shop for and purchase at least 10 unique items that are advertised in the Competitor Print Ad (there are purchase restrictions). Your purchase must total at least $40.

You will be required to take (2) photos, and answer (2) questions confirming the ad dates, ad retailer, and receipt for your shopping trip.

Please, please, please read and follow instructions carefully.  We want to pay you for this job.

However, you will NOT be paid for this job if you do NOT complete it correctly. And we will NOT reimburse you for your shopping trip.

This receipt should not be entered into Savings Catcher."}

Okay. It's time to start shopping! But before you do, there are a few rules...

If I were you, I would keep these instructions open as you shop.

You are required to purchase at least 10 Unique items. No two items can be the same. And you must spend at least $40. 

Remember, we will pay you $6 for completing this job correctly. And reimburse you $45 if you complete this job as requested. If you do not follow these instructions, you will not be paid or reimbursed for your shopping trip.

 

There are some restrictions on what you CAN buy.

  1. You are ONLY allowed to purchase items that are equivalent to items that are included in the Competitive Print Ad.
  2. Only purchase items that have a SPECIFIC PRICE listed. Like:
    1. A specific item for a specified price.
    2. Specific items with preferred shopping card prices.
    3. "Buy One, Get One" with a specific price.

There are also some restrictions on what you CANNOT buy.

  1. You can not purchase items that require a coupon.
  2. You can not buy any of the folllowing types of items:
    1. Fresh Produce or Meat items
    2. Alcohol
    3. Floral Items
    4. Store Brands
  3. You can not buy items that do not have a specific price. Like:
    1. Percentage off items (ex. "All mascara, 40% off" or "Spend $10, get 10% off")
    2. Items that require a separate purchase to get the ad price (ex. "Buy X to get Y for $Z")
    3. Items that require a purchase to get free product with no actual price (ex. "Buy both X and Y to get Z for free")
    4. Items with no actual price and require purchase to recieve a gift card (ex. "Buy X to get a $ Gift Card")
    5. Going out of business price promotions
    6. Store Brand price promotions (Great Value, etc.)
    7. "Buy One, Get One" with no listed price

 

Please complete your shop according to the above instructions. This is the most important part of the job.

We CAN NOT PAY YOU if you do not complete this part correctly.

Please proceed with checking out.  But please only include items for this job on this receipt.

As you know, you are required to purchase at least 10 unique items that are advertised in the Competitor Print Ad.

Once you have checked out, we need to see your receipt in order to verify that you have purchased at least 10 unique items and spent at least $40.

Clearly capture the entire receipt.  We MUST be able to see:

  • All four corners of the receipt
  • Items (must be legible)
  • Date and time (must be legible)

*This step is REALLY important. You will not be paid for this job if we can't perfectly see ALL elements of the receipt.

{"all_questions_require_answer":true,"name":"WMT SAN DIEGO - Walmart Saver QC Shop Project - 4.6.14 Week 10 (Ralph’s)","qc_comments":"All four corners of the receipt must be visible, otherwise DENY.","objective":"","id":67688,"instructions":"*IT IS CRITICAL THAT YOU READ AND FOLLOW THESE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY.* 

*You will NOT be paid for this job if you do NOT complete it correctly. *

*This job will require you to purchase at least $40 worth of items. 

If you complete the job as requested, we will pay you $6. In addition, we will reimburse you with $45 to cover the cost of your purchases! Can you say, "Free Shopping Trip to Walmart!"*

*The $45 payment transaction may take a few days to show up in your Field Agent account.*


INSTRUCTIONS:

Before going to the WALMART location listed, please pick up a current Print Ad (circular) from the following retailer (Competitor Store):

   - Ralph’s

*You will need a printed copy. A digital version will NOT work.

Please make sure that the Print Ad is from a store that is within 5 miles of the Walmart location you will be shopping. One of the above stores should be nearby.

There are additional instructions in the job that will direct you through this shopping trip. 

In general, you will shop for and purchase at least 10 unique items that are advertised in the Competitor Print Ad (there are purchase restrictions). Your purchase must total at least $40.

You will be required to take (2) photos, and answer (2) questions confirming the ad dates, ad retailer, and receipt for your shopping trip.

Please, please, please read and follow instructions carefully.  We want to pay you for this job.

However, you will NOT be paid for this job if you do NOT complete it correctly. And we will NOT reimburse you for your shopping trip.

This receipt should not be entered into Savings Catcher."}

Okay. It's time to start shopping! But before you do, there are a few rules...

If I were you, I would keep these instructions open as you shop.

You are required to purchase at least 10 Unique items. No two items can be the same. And you must spend at least $40. 

Remember, we will pay you $6 for completing this job correctly. And reimburse you $45 if you complete this job as requested. If you do not follow these instructions, you will not be paid or reimbursed for your shopping trip.

 

There are some restrictions on what you CAN buy.

  1. You are ONLY allowed to purchase items that are equivalent to items that are included in the Competitive Print Ad.
  2. Only purchase items that have a SPECIFIC PRICE listed. Like:
    1. A specific item for a specified price.
    2. Specific items with preferred shopping card prices.
    3. "Buy One, Get One" with a specific price.

There are also some restrictions on what you CANNOT buy.

  1. You can not purchase items that require a coupon.
  2. You can not buy any of the folllowing types of items:
    1. Fresh Produce or Meat items
    2. Alcohol
    3. Floral Items
    4. Store Brands
  3. You can not buy items that do not have a specific price. Like:
    1. Percentage off items (ex. "All mascara, 40% off" or "Spend $10, get 10% off")
    2. Items that require a separate purchase to get the ad price (ex. "Buy X to get Y for $Z")
    3. Items that require a purchase to get free product with no actual price (ex. "Buy both X and Y to get Z for free")
    4. Items with no actual price and require purchase to recieve a gift card (ex. "Buy X to get a $ Gift Card")
    5. Going out of business price promotions
    6. Store Brand price promotions (Great Value, etc.)
    7. "Buy One, Get One" with no listed price

 

Please complete your shop according to the above instructions. This is the most important part of the job.

We CAN NOT PAY YOU if you do not complete this part correctly.
